## ServiceFlow Features

### Authentication & Access Control
- User registration with department selection
- Email/password login via Auth.js v5 credentials
- JWT session management
- Role-based access: Admin and User roles
- Middleware-enforced route protection
- Admin-only routes (/admin/**)

### Service Request Management
- Create service requests with full detail
- Auto-generated request codes (SR-YYYY-NNNN)
- Request fields: title, description, type, department, requester, date, priority, status
- Request types: IT Support, Maintenance, Office, Document Processing, General
- Priority levels: Low, Medium, High, Urgent
- Status workflow: Pending → In Progress → Resolved → Closed / Cancelled
- Soft delete (deleted_at timestamp, data preserved)
- Edit own requests (users) or any request (admin)

### Request List & Search
- Paginated table with 10 records per page
- Search by title, request code, department
- Filter by: status, request type, department, priority
- URL-based filter state (shareable/bookmarkable)

### Dashboard
- Summary cards: Total, Pending, In Progress, Resolved
- Pie chart: Requests by status
- Bar chart: Requests by type
- Bar chart: Requests by department
- Bar chart: Monthly trend (last 6 months)
- Recent requests list with quick access

### Reports
- Date range filter (from/to)
- Tabs: By Status, By Type, By Department, By Priority
- Each tab: Chart + breakdown table with percentages
- Summary totals

### Admin User Management
- View all users with role badges
- Promote/demote user roles
- Delete users (cannot delete self)
- Create new users with role assignment

### UX & Design
- Responsive layout (mobile drawer sidebar, desktop sidebar)
- Loading skeleton states
- Error boundaries per route
- Toast notifications for all mutations
- Clean business-professional design
